---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.endsWith('/')
	? import.meta.env.BASE_URL
	: `${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}/`;
---

<Layout title="Slashtalk — we built a presence dock for our remote team. Here's why.">
	<div class="min-h-screen bg-white text-neutral-900">
		<header
			class="mx-auto flex max-w-6xl items-center justify-between px-6 py-6"
		>
			<a href="/" class="flex items-center gap-2.5">
				<img
					src="/favicon.svg"
					alt=""
					width="28"
					height="28"
					class="rounded-md"
				/>
				<span class="text-base font-semibold tracking-tight"
					>Slashtalk</span
				>
			</a>
			<nav class="flex items-center gap-2 sm:gap-7">
				<a
					href="/blog"
					class="hidden text-sm font-medium text-neutral-600 transition hover:text-neutral-900 sm:inline"
					>Blog</a
				>
				<a
					href="https://github.com/HereNotThere/slashtalk"
					class="hidden text-sm font-medium text-neutral-600 transition hover:text-neutral-900 sm:inline"
					>GitHub</a
				>
				<button
					type="button"
					data-download
					class="rounded-full bg-neutral-900 px-4 py-2 text-sm font-medium text-white transition hover:bg-neutral-700"
				>
					Download
				</button>
			</nav>
		</header>

		<main class="mx-auto max-w-2xl px-6 pt-8 pb-16 sm:pt-12 sm:pb-24">
			<article class="space-y-7 text-[17px] leading-[1.7] text-neutral-700">
				<h1
					class="text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-neutral-900 sm:text-4xl"
				>
					We built a presence dock for our remote team. Here's why.
				</h1>

				<p>
					Our team had a coordination problem we kept trying to solve with
					more talking.
				</p>

				<p>
					We're small, fully remote, and we ship fast. Because we aren't 100%
					relying on tickets, we pinged each other constantly — <em
						class="italic text-neutral-900">"hey, are you on this?"</em
					>. We did daily
					standups, status threads, Slack channels. People wouldn't pay
					attention and the noise became louder, not clearer.
				</p>

				<p>
					The tools we'd inherited were built for the old way of work.
					Standups assume your whole day of work fits into two sentences. Ticket tracking assumes people should only work on what they're assigned. Slack channel updates assume people read them. None of
					those assumptions hold at the speed small teams are moving today.
				</p>

				<p>So we built the thing we wished we had.</p>

				<hr class="my-12 border-neutral-200" />

				<p>
					Slashtalk is a floating dock that sits on top of your desktop.
				</p>

				<figure class="my-10">
					<img
						src={`${base}screenshot-dock.png`}
						alt="The Slashtalk dock — a row of teammate avatars floating above your other apps."
						class="w-full rounded-xl"
					/>
				</figure>

				<p>
					Each teammate is a card which shows what they're shipping: recent
					PRs, active sessions. The question "what
					are you working on?" stops getting asked because the answer is
					always on your dock.
				</p>

				<figure class="my-10 flex justify-center">
					<img
						src={`${base}screenshot-card.png`}
						alt="A teammate card showing recent sessions, current branch, and token usage."
						class="w-full max-w-sm rounded-xl"
					/>
				</figure>

				<p>
					PMs or CEOs constantly pinging developers? They can just go ask. The answers come from
					real code, not a guess.
				</p>

				<figure class="my-10">
					<img
						src={`${base}screenshot-ask.png`}
						alt="The Ask window — a chat interface synthesizing what the team shipped this week."
						class="w-full rounded-xl"
					/>
				</figure>

				<p>
					When two of us start editing files that are about to collide,
					both our cards flag it. We catch conflicts in the five minutes
					they're being created.
				</p>

				<p>
					And we purposely left chat or messaging out of this product. We all have enough of those apps on our computers.
				</p>

				<p>
					We've been on it ourselves for a while now, and so far, we're shipping more with fewer interruptions and it's been delightful to feel like you're working alongside your teammates even when you're not physically together.
				</p>

				<p>
					If you're on a small team shipping fast with AI and the
					coordination is starting to fray — try it and let us know what
					you think.
				</p>

				<div id="install" class="scroll-mt-8 pt-4">
					<div class="flex flex-col items-center gap-4 sm:flex-row">
						<button
							type="button"
							data-download
							class="inline-flex items-center gap-2.5 rounded-full bg-neutral-900 px-7 py-3.5 text-base font-medium text-white shadow-sm transition hover:bg-neutral-700"
						>
							<svg
								viewBox="0 0 24 24"
								fill="currentColor"
								width="18"
								height="18"
								aria-hidden="true"
							>
								<path
									d="M16.365 1.43c0 1.14-.46 2.235-1.21 3.034-.808.86-2.121 1.527-3.207 1.443-.142-1.078.452-2.21 1.18-2.92.815-.79 2.21-1.398 3.237-1.557zm3.926 17.14c-.612 1.345-.905 1.946-1.694 3.137-1.103 1.661-2.66 3.731-4.59 3.748-1.715.016-2.156-1.122-4.485-1.107-2.328.014-2.812 1.13-4.527 1.114-1.93-.018-3.404-1.882-4.508-3.543-3.085-4.65-3.41-10.106-1.506-13.005 1.353-2.06 3.488-3.265 5.495-3.265 2.043 0 3.328 1.122 5.022 1.122 1.643 0 2.643-1.124 5.014-1.124 1.789 0 3.685.974 5.034 2.66-4.426 2.42-3.703 8.747.745 10.263z"
								></path>
							</svg>
							Download for macOS
						</button>
						<span class="text-sm text-neutral-500">
							Free · macOS 13+ · Apple Silicon &amp; Intel
						</span>
					</div>
				</div>
			</article>
		</main>

		<footer
			class="mx-auto flex max-w-6xl flex-col items-center justify-between gap-4 border-t border-neutral-200 px-6 py-8 text-sm text-neutral-500 sm:flex-row"
		>
			<div>
				Slashtalk — from <a
					href="https://x.com/TownsLabs"
					class="text-neutral-700 underline decoration-neutral-300 underline-offset-4 transition hover:decoration-neutral-700"
					>Towns Labs</a
				>
			</div>
			<div class="flex items-center gap-6">
				<a href="/blog" class="transition hover:text-neutral-900"
					>Blog</a
				>
				<a
					href="https://github.com/HereNotThere/slashtalk"
					class="transition hover:text-neutral-900">GitHub</a
				>
				<a
					href="https://x.com/TownsLabs"
					class="transition hover:text-neutral-900">Twitter</a
				>
			</div>
		</footer>
	</div>
</Layout>

<script>
	document
		.querySelectorAll<HTMLButtonElement>('[data-download]')
		.forEach((button) => {
			button.addEventListener('click', () => {
				console.log('[slashtalk] Download for macOS clicked');
			});
		});
</script>
